reviews.review_text: the unplugged sound of the guitars works well but especially choice are the great vocals in this show .  even the songs you may not love sure sound great
Crispy Sets I do concur Grasshopper.. Tasty Bob on acoustic..

I am on an amazing journey I am listening to all 1994 shows in order, mining for gold. 

Like the previous night, the band is lacking some pep in their step. Jerry does go off a bit at the end of Stella Blue, and the China>Rider is nice. Very good Broken Arrow for the Phil Zone, cool Eternity, and overall the vocals were spectacular thanks to the in-ear monitors.

The Drums>Space was a major highlight for me here.
